{"word":"H5433 - סָבָא - çâbâʼ - saw-baw' - Drunkard","slug":"H5433","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">סָבָא</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>çâbâʼ"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>saw-baw'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Drunkard"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E1;&#x05D1;&#x05D0; - sa&#x0302;ba&#x0302;'</b> - <i>saw-baw'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>quaff</i> to satiety, that is, <i>become tipsy: - </i>drunkard, fill self, Sabean, [wine-] bibber."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H5434\">H5434</a>, <a href=\"#/H5435\">H5435</a>, <a href=\"#/H5436\">H5436</a>"}]}